---
// About section — facts cross-checked against DanielRoytel_Resume.pdf
// (career start date, current stack, certifications).
---

<section id="about" class="about" data-sr>
  <h2 class="numbered-heading">About Me</h2>
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="text">
      <p>
        Hello! My name is Daniel. I&rsquo;m a Data Engineer with over 10 years across banking and
        wagering. I started at <a href="https://www.nab.com.au" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">NAB</a>
        in 2012 working in customer service and internet-banking support, then moved into reporting
        and analytics in 2014 — building SQL and Excel reporting for banker performance. From there
        I moved into data design and then data engineering on the Personal Bank Data &amp; Analytics
        platform.
      </p>
      <p>
        Today, I&rsquo;m a Data Engineer on the Data Platforms team at
        <a href="https://www.sportsbet.com.au" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Sportsbet</a>, where
        I build and operate the AWS Deltalake Platform (ADP) — Spark pipelines for billion-record
        migrations, event-driven Kafka ingestion, and the CloudFormation and GitHub Actions
        tooling that keeps it shipping.
      </p>
      <p>Here are a few technologies I&rsquo;ve been working with recently:</p>
      <ul class="skills-list">
        <li>Python / PySpark</li>
        <li>SQL</li>
        <li>Apache Spark</li>
        <li>Databricks</li>
        <li>AWS Glue</li>
        <li>Apache Kafka</li>
        <li>Apache Airflow</li>
        <li>Terraform</li>
        <li>Docker</li>
        <li>GitHub Actions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>A few certifications along the way:</p>
      <ul class="certs-list">
        <li>AWS Certified Developer &ndash; Associate</li>
        <li>Databricks Certified Data Engineer Associate</li>
        <li>Azure Data Engineer Associate</li>
        <li>Azure Developer Associate</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="pic">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <img class="img" src="/images/me.jpg" alt="Headshot" loading="lazy" width="500" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about { max-width: 900px; }
  .about .inner {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3fr 2fr;
    grid-gap: 50px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about .inner { display: block; }
  }

  .skills-list,
  .certs-list {
    display: grid;
    grid-gap: 0 10px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 20px 0 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    list-style: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fz-xs);
  }
  .skills-list {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(140px, 200px));
  }
  .certs-list {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  .skills-list li,
  .certs-list li {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .skills-list li::before,
  .certs-list li::before {
    content: '▹';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--orange);
    font-size: var(--fz-sm);
    line-height: 12px;
  }

  .pic {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 300px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pic {
      margin: 50px auto 0;
      width: 70%;
    }
  }

  .wrapper {
    box-shadow: 0 10px 30px -15px var(--navy-shadow);
    transition: var(--transition);
    display: block;
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    background-color: var(--orange);
  }
  .wrapper:hover,
  .wrapper:focus {
    outline: 0;
  }
  .wrapper:hover::after,
  .wrapper:focus::after {
    top: 15px;
    left: 15px;
  }
  .wrapper:hover .img,
  .wrapper:focus .img {
    filter: none;
    mix-blend-mode: normal;
  }
  .wrapper .img {
    position: relative;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    mix-blend-mode: multiply;
    filter: grayscale(100%) contrast(1);
    transition: var(--transition);
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  .wrapper::before,
  .wrapper::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    position: absolute;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    transition: var(--transition);
  }
  .wrapper::before {
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    background-color: var(--navy);
    mix-blend-mode: screen;
  }
  .wrapper::after {
    border: 2px solid var(--orange);
    top: 20px;
    left: 20px;
    z-index: -1;
  }
</style>
